repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
This does a few things:
* Adds a `--no-compile` argument to `runtests.py` to let you go through the test suite without recompiling anything but just rerunning the tests. Also adapt end to end tests to try to make them work in this style by identifying the "compile" steps. I'm pretty confident that this mostly works.
* Tries to to rerun the tests on higher Python versions in the CI for the Limited API jobs. I'm not confident that this is going to work first go.
* Adds Limited API 3.9 to the matrix (if nothing else, it's what we ship Cython with on the less important platforms). To keep the same number of jobs I've dropped Limited API 3.13 since I don't think much changed there. But we can always revise this.

commit.message:

The intention is to use this to test the Limited API more
